com.niklasarndt.healthchecksio

Interface HealthchecksManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HealthchecksManagerImpl

    public interface HealthchecksManager

    Utilizes the Management API to manage or read checks/pings on a healthchecks.io host.

    Since:
    1.0.1

      • getCheck

        default CompletableFuture<Check> getCheck(Check check)

        Requests a Check from the API again, based on the UUID or unique key.

        Parameters:
        check - The already existing check with a valid UUID or unique key.
        Returns:
        A Check, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.

      • getCheck

        Parameters:
        key - A valid UUID or unique key for a check.
        Returns:
        A Check, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.

      • getCheckByName

        CompletableFuture<Check> getCheckByName(String name)

        Requests a Check from the API, based on the name provided.

        Please note that this method requests all checks from the API, since no query method by name exists natively.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the check.
        Returns:
        A Check, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution, or null if no check with that name exists.

      • getExistingChecks

        CompletableFuture<Check[]> getExistingChecks(String... tags)

        Requests multiple Checks from the API.

        If you want to do this (optional), you can specify multiple tags. If specified, the healthchecks.io instance will only return checks which have all the tags provided.

        Parameters:
        tags - (optional) The tags which all returned checks should have
        Returns:
        An array of Checks, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.

      • createCheck

        CompletableFuture<Check> createCheck(Check check)

        Creates a new Check based on the input data provided.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        To use this method, create a new Check via new Check() and fill in the values you want to change (e.g. name, schedule). The library/ healthchecks.io will fill in the default values for all the other data automatically.

        Invalid data will lead to a failing request.

        Parameters:
        check - The raw check data (doesn't need to contain any data at all).
        Returns:
        A Check, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (healthchecks.io rejects the request).

      • updateCheck

        CompletableFuture<Check> updateCheck(Check check)

        Updates an already Check.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getCheck(String) and edit in the values you want to change (e.g. description, schedule). The library/ healthchecks.io will fill in the default values for all the other data automatically.

        Some data (like the ping url) will obviously not be sent back to the healthchecks.io instance, since these values are static.

        Invalid data will lead to a failing request.

        Parameters:
        check - The altered Check data.
        Returns:
        The updated Check, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you won't have the UUID or the permission to update checks).

      • pauseCheck

        default CompletableFuture<Check> pauseCheck(Check check)

        Pauses a Check.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getCheck(String) and then invoke this method.

        Parameters:
        check - The raw check data (doesn't need to contain any data at all).
        Returns:
        The Check which has just been paused, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you don't have an UUID).

      • pauseCheck

        CompletableFuture<Check> pauseCheck(String uuid)

        Pauses a Check with the UUID provided.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        An invalid UUID will lead to a failing request.

        Parameters:
        uuid - A valid UUID for a Check you have control over.
        Returns:
        The Check which has just been paused, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you don't have an UUID).

      • deleteCheck

        default CompletableFuture<Check> deleteCheck(Check check)

        Deletes a Check. The check data will be permanently gone, so make sure you know what you are doing.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getCheck(String) and then invoke this method.

        Parameters:
        check - The obtained check (it's UUID is the important data).
        Returns:
        The Check which has just been deleted, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you don't have an UUID).

      • deleteCheck

        CompletableFuture<Check> deleteCheck(String uuid)

        Deletes a Check with the specified UUID. The check data will be permanently gone, so make sure you know what you are doing.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        Parameters:
        uuid - A valid UUID for a Check you have control over.
        Returns:
        The Check which has just been deleted, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you don't have an UUID).

      • getPings

        default CompletableFuture<Ping[]> getPings(Check check)

        Lists all Pings of a Check. If you use a free account, this number is limited to 100, otherwise to 1000.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getCheck(String) and then invoke this method.

        Parameters:
        check - The obtained check (it's UUID is the important data).
        Returns:
        An array of Pings, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you don't have an UUID).

      • getPings

        CompletableFuture<Ping[]> getPings(String uuid)

        Lists all Pings of a Check with the specified UUID. If you use a free account, this number is limited to 100, otherwise to 1000.

        Not available in read-only mode!

        Parameters:
        uuid - A valid UUId for a Check you have control over.
        Returns:
        An array of Pings, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.
        Throws:
        UnauthorizedException - If you are in read-only mode (you don't have an UUID).

      • getFlips

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getExistingChecks(String...) and then invoke this method.

        Parameters:
        check - An already existing Check.
        Returns:
        An array of StatusFlips, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.

      • getFlips

        default CompletableFuture<StatusFlip[]> getFlips(Check check,
                                                 long seconds)

        Lists all StatusFlips of a Check (in the last seconds seconds).

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getExistingChecks(String...) and then invoke this method.

        Parameters:
        check - An already existing Check.
        seconds - The maximum amount of seconds which have passed since the status flip.
        Returns:
        An array of StatusFlips, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.

      • getFlips

        default CompletableFuture<StatusFlip[]> getFlips(Check check,
                                                 long start,
                                                 long end)

        Lists all StatusFlips of a Check (in the time frame).

        To use this method, obtain a Check, e.g. via getExistingChecks(String...) and then invoke this method.

        The parameters are UNIX timestamps (e.g. System.currentTimeMillis()).

        Parameters:
        check - An already existing Check.
        start - The start date of the time frame (UNIX timestamp).
        end - The end date of the time frame (UNIX timestamp).
        Returns:
        An array of StatusFlips, wrapped in a CompletableFuture object for async execution.

      • getFlips
